cs.SE, cs.HC, cs.VR, cs.PL, cs.SD

Reasoning: 

- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a tool to support developers in analyzing the performance of software systems. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of an immersive augmented reality device and reports on early feedback on the usability of the visualization tool. 
- cs.VR (Virtual Reality) is another possible category as the paper uses an immersive augmented reality device to display the visualization. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses the impact of code changes on the performance of software systems. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) is also less likely but still possible as the paper proposes a tool to support developers in their development flow.
